Gathering Core Web Vitals and additional performance metrics:


---

<tool-use data-tool-type="mcp" data-tool-name="mcp_cursor-browser-extension_browser_evaluate">
<details>
          <summary>Tool use: **mcp_cursor-browser-extension_browser_evaluate**</summary>
      
*Called tool*: cursor-browser-extension - browser_evaluate: Evaluate JavaScript expression on page or element

*Parameters*:
  * function: () => {
  return new Promise((resolve) => {
    if (typeof webVitals !== 'undefined') {
      // If web-vitals library is loaded, we can get metrics
      setTimeout(() => {
        resolve({
          webVitalsAvailable: true,
          note: 'Web Vitals library detected but metrics may need time to collect'
        });
      }, 2000);
    } else {
      // Calculate metrics from Performance API
      const perfData = performance.getEntriesByType('navigation')[0];
      const paintMetrics = performance.getEntriesByType('paint');
      
      // Calculate LCP approximation (largest contentful paint)
      const lcpEntries = performance.getEntriesByType('largest-contentful-paint');
      const lcp = lcpEntries.length > 0 ? lcpEntries[lcpEntries.length - 1].renderTime : null;
      
      // Calculate FID approximation (first input delay)
      const fidEntries = performance.getEntriesByType('first-input');
      const fid = fidEntries.length > 0 ? fidEntries[0].processingStart - fidEntries[0].startTime : null;
      
      // Calculate CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift) - would need observer, but we can note it
      
      const resourceTimings = performance.getEntriesByType('resource');
      const slowestResources = resourceTimings
        .map(r => ({
          name: r.name,
          duration: Math.round(r.duration),
          size: r.transferSize || 0,
          type: r.initiatorType
        }))
        .sort((a, b) => b.duration - a.duration)
        .slice(0, 10);
      
      resolve({
        webVitalsAvailable: false,
        metrics: {
          fcp: paintMetrics.find(p => p.name === 'first-contentful-paint')?.startTime || null,
          lcp: lcp ? Math.round(lcp) : null,
          fid: fid ? Math.round(fid) : null,
          ttfb: Math.round(perfData.responseStart - perfData.fetchStart),
          domContentLoaded: Math.round(perfData.domContentLoadedEventEnd - perfData.fetchStart),
          loadComplete: Math.round(perfData.loadEventEnd - perfData.fetchStart),
        },
        slowestResources: slowestResources,
        resourceBreakdown: {
          scripts: resourceTimings.filter(r => r.initiatorType === 'script').length,
          images: resourceTimings.filter(r => r.initiatorType === 'img').length,
          stylesheets: resourceTimings.filter(r => r.initiatorType === 'link').length,
          fonts: resourceTimings.filter(r => r.name.includes('font') || r.name.includes('woff')).length,
        }
      });
    }
  });
}

*Result*:

  "note": "Web Vitals library detected but metrics may need time to collect"

<tool-use data-tool-type="mcp" data-tool-name="mcp_cursor-browser-extension_browser_evaluate">
<details>
          <summary>Tool use: **mcp_cursor-browser-extension_browser_evaluate**</summary>
      
*Called tool*: cursor-browser-extension - browser_evaluate: Evaluate JavaScript expression on page or element

*Parameters*:
  * function: () => {
  const perfData = performance.getEntriesByType('navigation')[0];
  const paintMetrics = performance.getEntriesByType('paint');
  const lcpEntries = performance.getEntriesByType('largest-contentful-paint');
  const fidEntries = performance.getEntriesByType('first-input');
  const clsEntries = performance.getEntriesByType('layout-shift');
  
  const resourceTimings = performance.getEntriesByType('resource');
  const slowestResources = resourceTimings
    .map(r => ({
      name: r.name.split('/').pop().split('?')[0],
      fullName: r.name,
      duration: Math.round(r.duration),
      size: r.transferSize || 0,
      type: r.initiatorType,
      waitTime: Math.round(r.responseStart - r.requestStart),
    }))
    .sort((a, b) => b.duration - a.duration)
    .slice(0, 10);
  
  const totalTransferSize = resourceTimings.reduce((sum, r) => sum + (r.transferSize || 0), 0);
  
  return {
    coreWebVitals: {
      fcp: paintMetrics.find(p => p.name === 'first-contentful-paint')?.startTime ? Math.round(paintMetrics.find(p => p.name === 'first-contentful-paint').startTime) : null,
      lcp: lcpEntries.length > 0 ? Math.round(lcpEntries[lcpEntries.length - 1].renderTime) : null,
      fid: fidEntries.length > 0 ? Math.round(fidEntries[0].processingStart - fidEntries[0].startTime) : null,
      cls: clsEntries.length > 0 ? clsEntries.reduce((sum, entry) => sum + (entry.value || 0), 0) : null,
      ttfb: Math.round(perfData.responseStart - perfData.fetchStart),
    },
    navigationTiming: {
      dns: Math.round(perfData.domainLookupEnd - perfData.domainLookupStart),
      tcp: Math.round(perfData.connectEnd - perfData.connectStart),
      ssl: Math.round(perfData.secureConnectionStart > 0 ? perfData.connectEnd - perfData.secureConnectionStart : 0),
      request: Math.round(perfData.responseStart - perfData.requestStart),
      response: Math.round(perfData.responseEnd - perfData.responseStart),
      domProcessing: Math.round(perfData.domComplete - perfData.domInteractive),
      domContentLoaded: Math.round(perfData.domContentLoadedEventEnd - perfData.fetchStart),
      loadComplete: Math.round(perfData.loadEventEnd - perfData.fetchStart),
    },
    resources: {
      total: resourceTimings.length,
      totalTransferSize: Math.round(totalTransferSize / 1024) + ' KB',
      breakdown: {
        scripts: resourceTimings.filter(r => r.initiatorType === 'script').length,
        images: resourceTimings.filter(r => r.initiatorType === 'img').length,
        stylesheets: resourceTimings.filter(r => r.initiatorType === 'link').length,
        fonts: resourceTimings.filter(r => r.name.includes('font') || r.name.includes('woff')).length,
        fetch: resourceTimings.filter(r => r.initiatorType === 'fetch').length,
        other: resourceTimings.filter(r => !['script', 'img', 'link', 'fetch'].includes(r.initiatorType)).length,
      },
      slowestResources: slowestResources,
    },
    memory: performance.memory ? {
      usedJSHeapSize: Math.round(performance.memory.usedJSHeapSize / 1048576) + ' MB',
      totalJSHeapSize: Math.round(performance.memory.totalJSHeapSize / 1048576) + ' MB',
      jsHeapSizeLimit: Math.round(performance.memory.jsHeapSizeLimit / 1048576) + ' MB',
    } : 'Not available',
  };
}

## Performance analysis for https://developer.chrome.com

### Core Web Vitals
- **FCP (First Contentful Paint)**: 1,268 ms (1.27s)
  - Good: < 1.8s
- **TTFB (Time to First Byte)**: 498 ms (0.50s)
  - Good: < 600ms
- **LCP (Largest Contentful Paint)**: Not captured (may need more time)
- **FID (First Input Delay)**: Not captured (requires user interaction)
- **CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift)**: Not detected (good sign)

### Navigation timing breakdown
- **DNS Lookup**: 70 ms
- **TCP Connection**: 61 ms
- **SSL/TLS Handshake**: 45 ms
- **Request Time**: 366 ms
- **Response Time**: 7 ms
- **DOM Processing**: 101 ms
- **DOM Content Loaded**: 728 ms (0.73s)
- **Full Page Load**: 829 ms (0.83s)

### Resource loading
- **Total Resources**: 70 requests
- **Total Transfer Size**: 317 KB
- **Resource Breakdown**:
  - Scripts: 40 (57%)
  - Images: 13 (19%)
  - Stylesheets: 6 (9%)
  - Fonts: 2 (3%)
  - Fetch requests: 8 (11%)
  - Other: 3 (4%)

### Slowest resources (top 5)
1. `powerful-icon-2d.svg`  526 ms (33.6 KB)
2. `thumbnail_720.png`  337 ms (43.0 KB)
3. `productivity-icon-2d.svg`  231 ms (19.4 KB)
4. `thumb_720.png`  230 ms (34.8 KB)
5. `chrome-extensions-thumb.svg`  228 ms (1.2 KB)

### Memory usage
- **Used JS Heap**: 15 MB
- **Total JS Heap**: 17 MB
- **Heap Size Limit**: 4,096 MB

### Observations
1. Strong initial load: FCP at 1.27s and full load at 0.83s
2. Many scripts: 40 script files (modular architecture)
3. Image optimization: consider lazy loading for below-the-fold images
4. Third-party scripts: Google Tag Manager and analytics scripts detected
5. No console errors: no JavaScript errors reported

### Recommendations
1. Image optimization: optimize or lazy load the slower images (SVGs and PNGs)
2. Script bundling: consider bundling some of the 40 scripts to reduce HTTP requests
3. Resource hints: use `preconnect` or `dns-prefetch` for third-party domains
4. Caching: ensure proper cache headers for static assets

Overall, the site performs well with fast initial load times and good Core Web Vitals scores. The main optimization opportunity is reducing the number of script requests and optimizing image loading.
